# Stake API Key Setup for Gambler.Bot

The user needs to obtain and configure the Stake.com API key to use Gambler.Bot for automated betting.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Security Warning**: Your API key grants access to your Stake account for betting and potentially other actions. **Never share your API Key or Session Token with anyone.** 

> [!NOTE]
> The long hex string you provided (96 characters) is likely your **Session Token** (cookie). While some bots use this, Gambler.Bot usually prefers the official **Stake API Key**.

---

## Proposed Instructions

### 1. How to find your Stake API Key
To obtain your official API key from Stake:
1. Log in to your account on [Stake.com](https://stake.com).
2. Click on your **User Profile icon** (top right).
3. Select **Settings** (or the gear icon).
4. Navigate to the **API** tab on the left sidebar.
5. If you have 2FA enabled, you will need to enter your code.
6. Look for the **API Key** section. If you haven't generated one yet, click **Generate**.
7. Copy the key.

### 2. How to use it in Gambler.Bot
1. Open **Gambler.Bot**.
2. Select **Stake** from the list of sites.
3. When the login screen appears, look for the field labeled **API Key** or **Token**.
4. Paste the key you copied from the Stake website.
5. Click **Login**.

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- The user should attempt to log in to Gambler.Bot using the official API key found in their Stake settings.
- Check if the "Logged In" status (the green user icon) appears in the bot's interface.
